# User Profile Badge & Hover Card on Public Board

Add a **profile visibility toggle** in user settings, replace the static "You" badge with the user's name (when toggled on), and show a rich **animated hover card** with user stats and an activity graph to any visitor hovering over the author badge on public items.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Settings location:** The sidebar currently has a "Settings" button that shows a toast "Settings coming soon!". This plan will create a proper **Settings modal/panel** triggered from that button. Is this the right location, or do you want settings elsewhere (e.g., a separate page)?

> [!WARNING]
> **Database migration required.** A new `user_settings` table and a `getUserProfile` public API will be added. You'll need to run the migration script after approval.

## Open Questions

1. **User avatar:** Clerk provides user profile images. Should we pull the avatar from Clerk for the hover card, or use a generated initial/icon?
2. **Name source:** Should the display name come from the existing `users.name` column (DB) or from Clerk's profile data?

